-- Oracle Forecasts 3rd-Qtr Adj. Profit Above Estimates
-- B y   P e t e r   J .   B r e n n a n
-- 2010-12-16T22:29:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-16/oracle-sees-adjusted-third-quarter-profit-of-48-cents-to-50-cents-a-share.html
Oracle Corp. forecast third-quarter
adjusted earnings per share of 48 cents to 50 cents on a
constant currency basis, according to a conference call. The
average estimate of analysts was 47 cents, according to
Bloomberg data.  Oracle said third-quarter revenue will increase 30 percent
to 34 percent on a constant currency basis.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter J. Brennan at 
 pbrennan3@bloomberg.net  